FT  10 JUL 93 / UK Company News: Sperati maintains improved trend
The improved trend of the last half of 1992 had continued in the current
year at CA Sperati (The Special Agency), the button and trimming merchant,
with pre-tax profits up from Pounds 12,302 to Pounds 35,899 in the half year
to April 30.
Sales rose by 28 per cent to Pounds 436,558 (Pounds 340,045). After tax of
Pounds 10,500 (Pounds 4,200) earnings per share were 25.4p (8.1p).
